We're Hiring » Helix TCS















































We're Hiring » Helix TCS




















Call us today (720) 328-5372




contact@helixtcs.com





































































Helix has an immediate need for Armed Security Operators in Colorado!
Helix TCS is searching for intelligent, courteous individuals with a friendly attitude, professional demeanor, great customer service skills, and the ability to communicate effectively.




The function of this position is the following:

To patrol assigned locations, enforce client, local, state and federal policy and regulations, and investigate and document all facility related incidents.
To ensure that the client, its associates, and facility personnel are provided with a safe and professional working environment.





A successful candidate must meet the following minimum standard qualifications:

Legally authorized to work in the United States.
At least 21 years of age or older as required by applicable law or contractual requirements.
Possess at least a high school education or equivalent (GED).
Demonstrate a stable work history.
Pass an extensive background screening which includes, but is not limited to, criminal background checks (local, state and federal with NO felonies or Class A or B misdemeanor convictions), drug test, and interviews.
Must be able to see, hear, speak and write clearly in order to communicate effectively with employees and/or other customers.
Must have a reliable mode of transportation.
For prior military, must have a copy of DD214 and an Honorable Discharge.
Previous contract services, security, military or law enforcement experience is desirable.






Why Helix TCS?
Find Support: Helix employees enjoy a friendly, “team” atmosphere where employees are trusted to do the assigned job. Flexible hours and scheduling to accommodate working professionals who plan on attending school and for reservist in the military and other public service careers.
Be Challenged: Our career progression opportunities create an environment where employees can thrive, succeed, and enhance their careers in the lawful cannabis industry.
Industry Education: Employees go through our industry leading 40 hr training academy. Helix’s academy is taught by Colorado POST certified instructors with over 50 years of training experience to include arrest control and defensive tactics.
Be Valued: We are more than just a job, we are a team!! It is the distinctive culture of Helix TCS and our dedication to our employees that set us apart from every other contract security company in the industry.





Employees with their Colorado issued Marijuana Enforcement Division Badge will receive a $150.00 signing bonus upon hire. Please send cover letter and resume to show contact info. Please list if you possess a Colorado Marijuana Enforcement Division Support badge.
Compensation:
$8.31 per hour during training
$12.00 per hour for part time employees
$12.00 per hour Night Shifts
$14.00 per hour salary (full time employees)




Salary: $12.00/hour
Job Location: Denver and Northern Colorado
Required experience:
Military or Law Enforcement: 1 year
Required education:
High school or equivalent
 
Send your resume to jobs@helixtcs.com 











  

